Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read the Prime Minister’s address for the latest information.

San Marino has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from San Marino, see Return to the UK
Entry and borders
Entry and exit into San Marino is currently prohibited except for reasons of healthcare, cross-border working or essential need.
Foreign nationals are permitted to cross the border into Italy in order to return home but need a valid passport and onward ticket.
Local measures
Extraordinary civil protection measures are in place, which include:
a ban on leaving the home except for essential reasons which may include work, healthcare or returning home
the suspension of all public gatherings, including sporting events, religious ceremonies, museums and cultural institutions
the closure of schools and higher education institutions
You can find more information on the emergency measures in place on the San Marino Ministry of Foreign Affairs website (in Italian and English).
Healthcare
If you believe you have symptoms, call San Marino’s coronavirus emergency number 0549 994001 (from 0800 – 1800) or 0549 888888 (from 1800 – 0800). Do not go directly to a hospital or healthcare facility.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
You can find more information about cases in San Marino on the TravelHealthPro website.
